This technique involves magnifying minute motions in videos to be able to see them with naked eyes. The basic idea of the project is to magnify adjacent frame differences. The crux of the project is to \u201csmartly\u201d get those differences so as to not magnify noise along with the signal, how to magnify motions that lie in a certain frequency range. The workflow of the algorithm is as follows - - We consider each of the frame independently. - We convert each frame from RGB to YIQ/NTSC image domain. - We create an image pyramid of each of the color channel independently. - We perform some temporal filtering(like IIR, butterworth etc) on the input frames - We magnify the difference that we get from the temporal filtering using spatial filtering techniques - We do some chromatic aberration of each of the color channel to reduce the noise components - We add the magnified difference back to the original image and convert the image back to RGB. This gives us the frame of the output video with magnified motion. To add the above functionality in the code, I have also implemented YIQ color domain in the VTK codebase. Also I have implemented image pyramid class since it did not exist in VTK. Please find the code in the link below. https://github.com/ashray/VTKCodes/tree/master/ImagePyramid An input video and magnified video is shown in the linked video below(or view it here https://youtu.be/hHwHAtGEbjs ). name: Dr. Kalapatapu Ravikiran Sharma
headline: Associate professor in management at Indian Institute of Health and Family Welfare, Government of Telangana, Hyderabad
summary: I am an associate professor in management at a Telangana state government public health training institute, namely Indian Institute of Health and Family Welfare (IIHFW), Hyderabad where I joined on August 2, 2006. I am engaged in the academic functions of training, teaching, research, evaluation, consultancy, advisory services, coordination, documentation, monitoring, field interventions, counselling, mentorship, coaching, supportive supervision, rapporteurship, advocacy, extension, outreach, institution building & professional contributions. My academic super-specialisation is health services management while my academic specialisations are planning & development, journalism, mass communication, human resource management, marketing management, and social work. I am a research doctorate, a double research postgraduate, a quadruple taught postgraduate, a quintuple professional title earner, a postgraduate certificate earner, a higher graduate, and a triple University Grants Commission (UGC) accredited lectureship qualifier. I am a qualified health scientist, a qualified management professional, a qualified development professional, a qualified journalist, a qualified mass communication professional, and a qualified social worker. I am a long duration program alumnus of the renowned Indian Institute of Management Ahmedabad (IIMA); a para-clinical doctorate from the prestigious Tata Institute of Social Sciences (TISS), Mumbai; a doctoral coursework product of the premier Indian Institute of Technology Roorkee (IITR); and a research postgraduate from the world-class Indian Institute of Technology Bombay (IITB). I am an England alumnus as I earned a five-month full-time postgraduate certificate in management from Southampton Institute, Nottingham Trent University, England. I have published 10 research papers in journals, 20 research papers in conference books, eight articles in newsletters, and five articles in magazines. I have presented 35 research papers in conferences, seminars, and workshops. I am an editorial board member of “Research Journal of Family, Community and Consumer Sciences”, an international peer-reviewed monthly journal.

summary: Hi, I'm Harshvardhan, a graduate in Electrical Engineering with a Computer Science minor from IIT Bombay, with a strong inclination for tackling complex, high-impact problems at the intersection of AI, Signal Processing, Product Management/ Strategy, and Business Strategy Consulting My portfolio bridges AI research and practical deployment, including Quantum Diffusion Models optimized for NISQ systems, low-error video denoising pipelines, LLM-based problem classification architectures, and RL frameworks for complex multi-variable simulations. I've had the opportunity to work on AI-first startups in Amsterdam, Singapore, and the US, leading ML product pipelines, market strategy projects, and AI product innovations, with achievements like Letters of Recommendation and Organizational awards, namely Roll of Honor and Institute Commendation. What drives me: The challenge of building scalable, intelligent systems that combine deep technical rigor with tangible, real-world product impact. Now, I'm looking for opportunities in: Machine Learning & AI Research (LLMs, RL, AI Safety), Quantitative Research and AI-based Trading, Product Analytics & Data Science for Tech Products, Applied ML for Signal & Speech Processing Keen to connect on: AI product innovation, consultative strategy engagements, ML research partnerships, RL-based systems, and roles within quant trading, AI-first startups, and tech venture investing.

name: Yogendra Pratap Singh
headline: BTech IIT Bombay
summary: I’m an IIT Bombay graduate with a deep curiosity for complex problems and a bias for purposeful action. My journey has been anything but linear, shaped by hands-on experiences in product strategy, business consulting, and more recently, an intense immersion into India’s governance and socio-economic systems through UPSC CSE preparation. Professionally, I’ve worked with teams at Bank of Baroda, where I helped chart a digital roadmap projected to scale users by 250%, and at Syscon Wires, where I enabled a 35% revenue boost and INR 40MN+ in savings through market and supply chain strategies. I was also extended a consulting offer from FSG, driven by my interest in social impact and structured problem-solving. During college, I led one of Asia’s largest student-run entrepreneurship bodies, forging VC partnerships, scaling outreach across 20+ states, and representing India at World Expo 2020 in Dubai. These experiences shaped my collaborative mindset, storytelling skills, and a strong ownership ethic. Outside of work, I enjoy strength training, long walks, and mentoring young aspirants, whether in career planning, competitive exams, or life transitions. I’m now pivoting into roles that allow me to work at the confluence of strategy, product, or policy and contribute meaningfully through insight, empathy, and execution. Let’s connect, especially if you’re building or solving something that matters.

name: Arushi Gandhi
headline: CEO at Ressl AI | Salesforce Enthusiast
summary: We're building to enable a future where Salesforce Implementation (or any enterprise ERP / CRM, for that matter), gets set up and ready to go in hours, definitely not months! I've built a CRM product before (fundinc.in), and I've felt the pain of professional services first-hand. We believe the future of IT services is going to look really really different, it won't be spent click-clacking on interfaces of bulky enterprise softwares. The vision we see and are actively enabling is one where you just prompt a system with your requirements. This system understands said instructions and converts them into configuration and metadata for Salesforce. The agentic enablement of Salesforce is here, and it's time software starts working for us and not the other way around. Write to me at arushi@ressl.ai to chat about anything startups, salesforce, and sales.

name: Shubham Jain
headline: Co-Founder at TradeReboot & Vasukam
summary: Technology is my passion, and its ability to solve real-world problems drives me forward. Innovative technologist and entrepreneur leveraging AI and Blockchain to revolutionize international trade processes. As Co-Founder and CTO of Trade Reboot, I'm on a mission to digitize and streamline complex industry workflows, driving efficiency and solving real-world challenges. Key Highlights: 1. IIT Bombay graduate with a BTech degree 2. 4+ years of expertise in finance and technology sectors 3. Founder of Vasukam, focused on reimaging social networking 4. Former management experience at Tata Projects and Daikin Japan 5. Developed a portable device for visually challenged individuals 6. Led UAV creation for search and rescue missions My journey from corporate management to entrepreneurship has been fueled by a passion for applying cutting-edge technology to practical problems. At Trade Reboot, we're not just optimizing processes – we're reimagining the future of international trade. Specialties: AI/ML, AWS, Process Automation, FinTech Innovation, Product R&D, Entrepreneurship Let's connect to discuss the future of trade, explore the potential of AI, or simply chat about leveraging technology for good.

headline: Product Manager @Flipkart | IIT Bombay
summary: I’m a Product Manager with 2+ years of experience at Flipkart, where I’ve led both consumer-facing and internal product initiatives - from crafting high-impact pricing tools to building intelligent platforms that automate workflows for teams. Whether I’m defining product strategy, designing intuitive experiences, or collaborating with engineers and analysts, my goal is always to create products that truly solve problems and scale with purpose. What I bring: 1. Strong foundations in product thinking, GTM planning, and user-centric design 2. Experience with data-heavy and AI-powered products 3. Proven ownership of 0-to-1 and 1-to-n product cycles 4. Cross-functional leadership and outcome-driven mindset Beyond work, I’m someone who’s deeply curious—especially about culture, people, and systems. I’m always looking to connect with teams building thoughtful, impactful products. If you're hiring or just want to talk product, let’s connect!

I hold a keen interest in pursuing roles encompassing Product Management, Growth & Strategy, and various facets of the business domain. My professional experiences includes expertise in product management, data analysis, and business development. I am keen to learn new things in the field above mentioned and build new relationships. Always curious and want to work with a diverse group of people that would help me grow in my field!

name: Aakash Kumar Singh
headline: Senior Data Scientist | IIT Bombay
summary: I am Aakash Kumar Singh, a Senior Data Scientist at Fincepta in Gurgaon, India. I hold a Bachelor of Technology degree from the Indian Institute of Technology Bombay, which I completed in June 2022. In my current role, I have been involved in various projects, including the development of a conversational AI bot powered by Flask, a Flask-based QnA bot, and an Audio Transcription & Summarization Project with AWS integration. Additionally, I engineered a Flask-based API for report analysis, integrating AWS Textract for PDF data extraction and developing a PyTorch-based language model for generating concise summaries from user prompts. I also developed a robust document classifier using DenseNet121, achieving exceptional accuracy through fine-tuning and data augmentation techniques. My technical skills include proficiency in Python, AWS, TensorFlow, and PostgreSQL, and I have expertise in areas such as Natural Language Processing, Deep Learning, and Computer Vision.

name: Sanskar Jain
headline: CEO at Entvin AI | AI for lifesciences | YCombinator | IIT Bombay
summary: Hi! I'm Sanskar, the Co-founder and CEO of Entvin, a Y Combinator-backed startup revolutionising the pharmaceuticals industry through innovative solutions. I come from a very small city called Shivpuri and have seen an entrepreneurial side in both my parents which is a very big reason why I am doing this. I am very close to nature and calm most of the time. Let me tell you a brief about Entvin: Entvin is a platform for R&D teams in pharmaceutical companies to accelerate drug development process. We are leveraging AI to help scientists at large pharmaceutical companies streamline their research work and bring drugs to patients across the world faster. At Entvin, we work with top 500 pharma companies to help their R&D teams automate a lot of their drug development processes. Apart from all this, I hold a B.Tech in Mechanical Engineering from IIT Bombay. I wore various hats during my college days. As a core group member of Mood Indigo, Asia's largest college cultural festival, I led a team of 30 to create memorable experiences. We are on a mission to transform the traditional pharmaceutical industry and leave a lasting impact. Let's connect and explore the possibilities together! Feel free to email me at sanskar@entvin.com Let’s catch up: https://calendly.com/entvin/entvin-discussion

name: Gaurav Tripathi
headline: Co-founder & Group CTO | Inventor (45 Patents) | BW Disrupt 40 Under 40
summary: From an early age, I was captivated by the power of technology to solve real-world problems. My journey began at IIT Bombay, where I pursued Aerospace Engineering, immersing myself in the science of innovation and problem-solving. Those formative years nurtured my curiosity and laid the foundation for a career driven by a passion for exploring how data and algorithms can improve lives. Today, as the Co-founder and Group CTO of Innoplexus AG, I lead a team dedicated to accelerating the discovery of newer, more efficacious therapies. At Innoplexus, we are at the forefront of AI innovation, empowering customers and partners to address some of the most pressing challenges in life sciences and healthcare. Over the years, I’ve had the privilege of building an IP portfolio of 145+ patents in areas like AI, ML, NLP, and information retrieval, with 45 patents listing me as an inventor. My professional journey also extends to my role as a board member at Amrit AG, where we’re creating a universal treatment discovery engine for diseases that have long eluded solutions. These roles have reinforced my passion for leveraging AI to solve complex problems and improve human longevity and well-being. Beyond work, I am passionate about community building. I launched the GPU Community, a thriving group of over 3,000 tech enthusiasts aiming to put Pune on the global AI map. Through initiatives like the TIP tech internship program, I enjoy mentoring aspiring entrepreneurs and emerging startups, helping shape the next generation of innovators. When I’m not immersed in technology or entrepreneurship, you’ll often find me trekking through nature, traveling to new places, or exploring new ideas through books. I deeply value time spent with family and strive to balance my professional aspirations with personal fulfillment.

name: Shikha
headline: Building Meeraq | E-Commerce | Jewellery (Sourcing, Design, Manufacturing) | Planning & Analytics | Coaching
summary: I am an experienced Merchandise Director with a proven track record in the luxury goods and jewelry industry, showcasing skills in Analytical Abilities, Coaching, Team Building, Product Assortment Planning, and Leadership. My journey began after completing my B.Tech and M.Tech degrees at the Indian Institute of Technology, Bombay. I initially embarked on a career as a software engineer at Version Data Services India, gaining expertise in ASP.Net, JavaScript, C/C++. After VDSI, I transitioned to Morgan Stanley Advantage Services, where I provided desk support from India, honing my skills in various programming interfaces including C/C++, Pearl, Python, Q/KDB, Excel-VBA and MS-SQL. My passion for creativity eventually led me to the world of Luxury and Fashion at Voylla, where I evolved from a Sourcing expert to the Head of Product Design & Sourcing. My role also encompassed Planning and Analytics at Voylla, offering me hands-on experience in e-commerce, retail, and marketing. My journey took a transformative turn when I delved into human resources, learning, and development through coach training at Coach-to-transformation. I was deeply impacted by the positive change it brought to my relationships, both personally and professionally. This experience motivated me to join Meeraq as Director for Growth, Planning & Analytics in January 2023. I'm a passionate and quick learner who is continually seeking opportunities for personal growth. Organizing and planning come naturally to me, and my affinity for numbers and creativity equips me to excel in analytics and data visualization. I have come to appreciate the transformative power of leadership and coaching in bringing out the best in people, and I'm exploring various avenues to contribute to society at my best.

name: Shreyas Chandgothia
headline: Analyst - Data Science at American Express | IIT Bombay '23
summary: I am Shreyas Chandgothia, currently working as an Analyst at American Express, Gurgaon. I have completed a B.Tech in Engineering Physics with a Minor in Computer Science, and an M.Tech in Artificial Intelligence & Data Science, from IIT Bombay. My home town is Chandigarh, India, where I have spent most of my childhood. Apart from my enthusiasm for Physics, I am deeply interested in algorithmic problem-solving inspired by tangible real-world applications. At IIT Bombay, I developed expertise in Machine Learning and Data Science through an Interdisciplinary Dual Degree Programme in the newly established Machine Intelligence department. I invested my 3rd and 4th year summers at IIT in corporate internships. One was as an Algorithmic Trader at Fox Trading Solutions, and the other was as a Data Analyst at Multiplier Technologies. The trading internship opened up the fascinating world of markets to me, and I became sure that I wanted to pursue a career at the intersection of Maths, Computer Science, and Finance. Coming to my hobbies, I love to watch and play sports. I follow cricket and tennis closely, and I’m always down to play badminton and table tennis with friends. Apart from this, I love interacting with and getting to know new people, which helps broaden my perspectives and understanding.

name: Bheeshm Sharma
headline: Doctoral Researcher | IEOR IIT Bombay | Exploring Deep Learning, Computer Vision & Generative AI.
summary: As a PhD candidate, I am passionate about using advanced deep-learning models to unlock the potential of medical imaging. My research focuses on analyzing large datasets from CT scans, MRIs, and X-rays to draw insights that can help identify and classify various diseases. By leveraging the power of deep learning and computer vision, I aim to develop algorithms that can make diagnostic processes more accurate and accessible. Apart from healthcare, I’m also exploring computer vision and generative AI applications for real-world challenges in image and video analysis. This broader focus allows me to apply cutting-edge techniques to solve diverse problems across various industries. Always eager to connect and discuss ideas around AI & Innovation.

name: Deevanshu
headline: PM - BharatNXT | IIT B | Fintech
summary: I don’t just ship features. I build systems and live with the fact that most good things happen by doing the same boring things better everyday.... and saara difference iss consistency se hi create hota hai.... At BharatNXT, I joined when we were 15 folks. today, we’re 70+ and have taken multiple 0→1 journeys in credit, payments, risk, and internal tools. From building seamless UX, Credit Card Bill Payment, RMS to automating credit profiling using SMS + Gmail + app data to starting Lending vertical, every product I’ve touched taught me something new: what breaks, what scales, and what no one tells you about. Before this, I started MagmaCray, helping SMBs cut ops costs and build lean tech. I chase elegance in code, clarity in docs, and silence on bike rides through the Himalayas....

name: Apoorv Anurag
headline: UX Designer at Optum, UHG | IDC IIT Bombay M.Des. Interaction Design | CEED 2021 AIR4
summary: Hello there! I'm currently a UX Designer at Optum, United Health Group at Hyderabad, Telangana. I am also a recent Master of Design graduate from IDC School of Design, IIT Bombay, specializing in Interaction Design, with a keen interest in design and research. My journey began with a bachelor's in Civil Engineering from IET Lucknow. However, my passion for creativity and problem solving with empathy led me to transition into the world of Interaction Design. I gave CEED in 2021 and achieved All India Rank 4 on my first attempt. Throughout my academic journey at IDC, I've been enthusiastic about learning new design skills, tools and exploring different subjects and domains while working on various projects. As I venture into the realm of UX Research and Design, I am committed to creating seamless and intuitive experiences for users by blending both analytical knowledge with creative thinking. When I'm not immersed in the world of design, you can find me indulging in my love for digital illustrations, exploring self-improvement books, doing some online course, weight training in gym, or enjoying some good feel-good movie. These diverse interests keep me grounded and inspired, as I believe that well-rounded experiences enhance my ability to empathize with users and create meaningful design solutions. I am excited to forge connections within the design community, collaborate on impactful projects, and contribute my skills to shape the future of user experiences. If you share a passion for UX research and design or have exciting ideas to explore, I'd love to connect and explore possibilities together!

headline: Founder at Rifa AI |  Building Conversations AI Platform

These agents work alongside your team, improving quality and efficiency as operations scale. What sets us apart: → Vertical agents are designed to handle workflows end-to-end. → Deep integrations, fully managed, no stitching tools together. → High customization to match your compliance and business logic. → Built-in experimentation to test, track, and move real KPIs. We’re focused on: → Voice AI with low latency, natural prosody, interruption handling, and backchanneling. → End-to-end automation across channels with deep integration and control. → Advances Analytics and Infrastructure to run experiments to improve KPIs and drive measurable business outcomes. Before Rifa, I worked across data science and software engineering, first in enterprise software, then in early-stage product teams. We’re hiring across product and engineering to build a best-in-class conversational AI platform. If you’re curious, let’s talk.

name: Rohit Shukla
headline: CXO - Legal Tech | Innovation | Law firm Management | GCC
summary: As the Chief Digital Officer at Khaitan & Company (KCO), I lead technology and innovation initiatives to enhance service delivery, optimize business operations, and drive digital transformation within professional services firms. I collaborate with management, cross-functional teams, and practitioners to implement a digital-first strategy that ensures KCO remains at the forefront of technology adoption. 🔹 Key Focus Areas ✔ Firm-wide Digital Transformation – Implementing enterprise Document Management Systems (DMS), streamlining workflows, and enhancing operational efficiency. ✔ AI & GenAI Strategy – Developing and deploying AI-driven solutions for legal research, contract automation, business intelligence, and decision support. ✔ Operational Efficiency & Process Automation – Leveraging technology and automation to optimize business operations, compliance, and knowledge management. ✔ Technology Adoption in Professional Services – Increasing the tech quotient across firms, ensuring seamless adoption of cutting-edge solutions. 🔹 Global Leadership in Technology & Professional Services Innovation With a career spanning technology leadership roles in professional services and legal tech, I bring a unique blend of expertise in enterprise IT, product innovation, and AI adoption. I have held roles at TCS, Wipro Technologies, Fidelity Investments, and LexisNexis, delivering high-impact digital initiatives. My global experience includes working and living in India, the USA, and the UK, driving large-scale transformation programs. 🔹 Notable Achievements ✅ Wipro – Established the global Revenue Assurance and Fraud Management practice for the telecom vertical. ✅ Fidelity Investments – Led India GCC’s largest product development outsourcing initiative and helped expand Fidelity’s business operations in India. ✅ LexisNexis – Spearheaded the successful launch of professional services and legal research products across India, Malaysia, Singapore, and Hong Kong. ✅ Legal & Professional Services Tech Entrepreneurship – Co-founded LegitQuest, launching an AI-based research and analytics platform. 🔹 Industry Engagement Actively contribute to industry thought leadership, startup collaborations, and AI-driven innovations. Of you are in startup ecosystem, I’ll be keen connect and identify areas of mutual learning and partnership.
